Arrays : these are used to store multiple values of a specific data type in a single variable


declaration of array :

int[] interger_array = {1,2,8,9,5};

int[] integer_array = new int[5];


char[] character_array = new char[5];


Accessing arrays : to access the data in array we should use the index of the elements


 int[] interger_array = {1,2,8,9,5};
 
 
 interger_array[0];
 
 
 interger_array[4];
 
 
 maximum index of an array = legth of array -1;
 
 
 Array_Name.length :: this will return the length of the array.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 